Secrets Stored in GitHub Secrets, never in code
Storage S3 bucket fully private
Suggested next steps for a production environment
Enable HTTPS with a real certificate (e.g. via AWS Certificate Manager + a Load Balancer, or Let’s Encrypt with
Certbot on the instance).
Rotate the SSH key periodically and consider replacing direct SSH deploys with AWS Systems Manager Session
Manager (removes the need for an open port 22 entirely).
Enable S3 bucket versioning and server-side encryption for the backup bucket.
Enable AWS CloudTrail for auditing API-level activity across the account.
